A universal two class classifier created using of BrainJS.
The web page has a canvas on which the user can draw any object.
After that, the user must press the "V" key and a pop-up window will appear asking whether the drawn object belongs to a specific class. 
When you click OK or Cancel, the machine assigns the object to one or another class. 
Then the machine converts the resulting pattern into a 25 by 25 matrix, where 1 are fully or partially filled cells. 
Based on the learned drawings, the machine is capable of correlating the drawn object with one or another class when pressing the "B" button. 
When you press the "C" button, the canvas is cleared
